  <!-- Story -->
  <section class="section story" role="region" aria-label="Our story">
    <div class="inner grid-2">
      <div>
        <span class="kicker">Family-Owned Since 1920</span>
        <h2>Old-World Skill. Modern Standards.</h2>
        <p>From the earliest days of icehouse lockers to today’s inspected facility, <strong>Prenzlow Meats</strong> has stood for straightforward quality: humane handling, careful trimming, and clean, freezer-ready packaging. We believe great meat starts with respect—for animals, for the craft, and for the families we serve.</p>
        <p>We’ve kept our promise simple for a century: be honest about what’s in the package, make it taste great, and treat every order like it’s going on our own table.</p>
        <p><em>What we don’t do:</em> flashy shortcuts, mystery blends, or race-to-the-bottom pricing. What we do every day: clean processes, consistent cuts, small-batch sausages, and dependable advice when you need it.</p>
      </div>
      <aside>
        <figure class="photo-card">
          <img src="/assets/locker-archive.jpg" alt="Historic photo of the original Prenzlow locker" />
          <figcaption class="photo-caption">A look back at the early locker days. Different tools—same promise.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Milestones -->
  <section class="section milestones" role="region" aria-label="Milestones">
    <div class="inner">
      <div>
        <h2>Highlights Through the Years</h2>
        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="t-item"><strong>1920</strong><span>Locker opens with hand-crank grinders and block ice.</span></div>
          <div class="t-item"><strong>1950s</strong><span>Smokehouse perfected for bacon and ring bologna.</span></div>
          <div class="t-item"><strong>1980s</strong><span>Custom cutting expands to quarter/half beef and whole hogs.</span></div>
          <div class="t-item"><strong>2000s</strong><span>Facility upgrades for modern food-safety and traceability.</span></div>
          <div class="t-item"><strong>Today</strong><span>Small-batch sausages, locker packs, and freezer-ready labeling.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
